This is a good ploy since it is a relatively cheap program, most people will not bother to try and get their money back at that point.  I understand that this is a paid app and it still not guaranteed to work on all phones from all carriers. However, there should be a trial period so you can test it and work out any issues with the developer before you have to purchase it.  If there was a trial period and this program had still failed I would not have been angry at all.  Also, ANY AND ALL potential issues whether directly caused by the program or external factors (like cell carriers etc...) should be noted in the comments.  Fabio says that this is not his responsibility.  That is NOT TRUE, it is a paid app which means the developer is responsible to alert you to all possible problems.

A couple of notes to the newbies out there:  1- Look up a set up guide online before contacting Fabio. There are plenty of step-by-step guides on the internet (got mine from Android forums) that will instruct you based on phone. Fabio probably gets thousands of emails, don't bug him if you can answer your own question with a simple google search.   2- [common sense] This app does not give you free internet, it lets you use your PHONE DATA SPEED as a router. So, if you have 2G/3G coverage, you will have 2G/3G speed internet. If you want this app to give you fast internet on laptop/computer/TV/etc make sure you have a 4G data plan.   So far I give this app a 5/5. Good work Fabio, i'm loving it.

Interface set to "wlan0",     Method 3 set to "HostApd",     Encryption set to "wpa2-psk",     Channel set to "1",     Drivers set to "nl80211"     and UNCHECK "HostApd Patch"
